#COVID19 lives on droplets in the lungs of people with the virus, even if they don’t have symptoms. When infected people breathe, the virus enters the air. If you can’t #StayHome, wear a mask/scarf/bandana, stay 6 feet apart, and wash your hands. #DontGoViral

#COVID19 vive de gotas en los pulmones de las personas con el virus incluso si no tienen síntomas.Cuando las personas contagiadas respiran, el virus entra al aire.Si no puedes quedarte en casa #StayHome, use una bufanda/pañuelo, manténgase a 6 pies de distancia y lávese las manos

Common symptoms of #COVID19 are fever, dry cough, & shortness of breath. If you have mild symptoms, call your doctor & #StayHome. If you develop serious symptoms, such as trouble breathing, pressure in the chest, or bluish lips or face, call your doctor & seek care immediately.

Spanish
Los síntomas comunes de #COVID19 son fiebre, tos seca y dificultad para respirar.Si tiene síntomas leves, llame a su médico y quedate en casa.Si desarrolla síntomas graves, como dificultad para respirar o presión en el pecho, busque atención médica de inmediato. #StayHome

post_text:
On June 12th, parents can access their child's STAAR results along with other resources to support summer learning at home by visiting www.texasassessment.gov.

You can find your child's access code in the purple box on the left side. You will enter the first 10 letters of your child's name, social security number, and date of birth. If you still have last year's results, the access code is on that, too.

Please don't hesitate to contact the school for questions.

Have a great summer!

PreK Round Up for SBISD will be May 2 beginning at 12:00. Enrolling your child in our PK allows him/her to start a path towards excellence with research-based curriculum while promoting social and emotional development.

Your child will need to he 4 years old by September 1.

Please bring the following when coming to the Round Up:
💙certified birth certificate
💙social security card
💙current immunization record.

Please contact the school for more information. (903)945-2460.

post_text: Franklin, TX was hit by a tornado last weekend. There was much damage throughout the town. At this time, the superintendent of Franklin ISD is asking for canned goods. She reported the local Food Bank was destroyed, and they have plenty of clothes at this time. If you would like to contribute food/gift cards, please drop them off at Mrs. Daniel's office by Thursday afternoon. Thank you for helping out those in need.
